sentences.en: A coalition government was formed after inconclusive elections.
sentences.cn: 选举没有结果，于是成立了一个联合政府。

sentences.en: Antifibrinolytics reduced bleeding in clinical trials, but animal study findings were inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 抗纤药在临床试验中减少出血, 但在动物实验中是非结论性.

sentences.en: Bloggs could take no satisfaction in the likelihood that Faber was dead. It was too inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 费伯可能死了,但布格斯对这个“可能”很不满足, 这太没把握啦.

sentences.en: But tests of possible drugs to enhance memory have been inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 但是提高记忆力的药物试验却毫无结果.
他称之为 “ 非决定性的 ”
这个成就显得多么不得要领!

sentences.en: Is the story inconclusive? What effect does it have on its audience?
sentences.cn: 这个故事是非决定性的 吗 ?它对读者有什么影响?

sentences.en: Most research on cancer has so far proved inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 迄今为止大多数关于癌症的研究仍无定论.

sentences.en: Petra is in the end when the construction is inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 佩特拉到底是什么时候建造的尚无定论.

sentences.en: Research has so far proved inconclusive.
Skeptics view most of these as inconclusive or otherwise consequential.
sentences.cn: 怀疑论的观点是大多数这些东西是作为随机而发生,或者是相因而生.

sentences.en: The evidence against the two men was inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 针对这两个人的不利证据并不令人信服。

sentences.en: The guiding precedent [ on the Commerce Clause ] is informative but inconclusive.
sentences.cn: ( 宪法的商业条款 ) 这一导向性的先例令人大开眼界但却带有不确定性.

sentences.en: The remainder of cases were inconclusive.
sentences.cn: 其余的那些事件则无法作出结论.

sentences.en: These findings are inconclusive and controversial and require further study.
sentences.cn: 但是这些发现是不确定的、有争议的、需要进一步研究.

sentences.en: What evidence is lacking, inconclusive, contradictory or too limited?
sentences.cn: 缺乏什麽证据?什麽是不确定的 、 矛盾的及太局限的?

words.tran_cn: 不确定的；非决定性的；无结果的

trans.tran_cn: 不确定的，非决定性的，无结果的，不能使人信服的，无效的，模棱两可
